ðŸ“¦ Software management:

Most Linux distros use package managers to install, update, or remove software.

Debian/Ubuntu: apt or apt-get

Fedora/RHEL/CentOS: dnf or yum

Example (Ubuntu/Debian):

bash
Copy
Edit
sudo apt update      # update package lists
sudo apt install vim # install vim editor
sudo apt remove vim  # remove vim

